*~

# Campsite logbook (SQLite database; ephemeral team coordination state)
# Anchored to repo root (`/campsites/`) so that `camp/src/campsites/`
# (the camp crate's campsite source modules) is NOT excluded.
/campsites/

# Scheduled-task lock dir (project-local Claude harness state; ephemeral)
.claude/

# AI-collaborator orientation file. Each developer may keep their own
# CLAUDE.md locally with paths/conventions tailored to their setup.
# README.md is the canonical project-orient for both humans and AI agents.
CLAUDE.md

# Design substrate. Lives locally for ongoing team development; not part of
# the published surface. Future externalization (sibling repo / GH Pages /
# etc.) is an open decision; for now substrate stays local.
docs/expedition/
sweeps/

# Empty/transient working dirs
.captured-shape/

# Camp coordination substrate — the camp/ Rust crate IS canonical dogfood
# content (antigen using antigen for its own team coordination), so the
# source + Cargo.toml + sidecars stay tracked. The per-role substrate
# folders (notebooks/insights/journals/etc.) hold team-ephemeral content
# and stay local-only.
camp/target/
camp/**/notebooks/
camp/**/insights/
camp/**/journals/
camp/**/random-thoughts/
camp/**/feature-ideas/
camp/**/experiments/

